---
import { AUTHOR_NAME, AUTHOR_URL, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';

const founderId = new URL('/#founder', Astro.site).toString();
const jsonLd = {
	'@context': 'https://schema.org',
	'@type': 'AboutPage',
	name: `About ${SITE_TITLE}`,
	url: new URL('/about/', Astro.site).toString(),
	mainEntity: {
		'@type': 'Organization',
		name: SITE_TITLE,
		url: Astro.site?.toString(),
		founder: {
			'@type': 'Person',
			'@id': founderId,
			name: AUTHOR_NAME,
			url: AUTHOR_URL,
			sameAs: [AUTHOR_URL],
		},
	},
};
---

<Layout
	title="About Vertical Agent Solutions"
	description="Who is behind Vertical Agent Solutions, what we publish, and how an autonomously-edited site stays honest."
	pubDate={new Date('June 20 2026')}
	isArticle={false}
>
	<script is:inline type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(jsonLd)} />
	<p>
		<strong>Vertical Agent Solutions</strong> exists to make the agentic wave legible to people who
		run real businesses — not just the engineers building the tools. The promise is simple: take what
		is genuinely useful about AI agents, strip away the noise, and explain it clearly enough to act
		on.
	</p>

	<h2>What we publish</h2>
	<p>
		Short, deeply-verified guides on adopting AI agents across industries. Every post goes through a
		review loop — fact-checked against real sources, simplified for a non-technical reader, and
		checked against everything we've already published so we never waste your time repeating
		ourselves.
	</p>

	<h2>Who runs this</h2>
	<!-- Photo goes here when available: a small portrait of Guillermo, floated
	     right of the paragraph below (e.g. <Image> from astro:assets). The
	     section is written to read complete without it. -->
	<p>
		<strong>{AUTHOR_NAME}</strong> is a software engineer building autonomous,
		verification-gated AI systems — agents that do real work, with the safety rules enforced in
		code rather than left to a model's judgment. He runs a portfolio of live agent systems, of
		which this site is one: its daily editor publishes, improves, and retires posts on its own,
		and he reviews everything it ships. He is based in the US, on Eastern time, and you can find
		his work on <a href={AUTHOR_URL}>GitHub</a>.
		{/* TODO: add LinkedIn URL once live — see hq/jobs/applications/linkedin-profile.md */}
	</p>

	<h2>How this site works</h2>
	<p>
		This site is itself a live agent system: an autonomous editor decides daily what to publish,
		improve, or retire, and a human reviews everything before it ships. If you're curious what
		that actually looks like under the hood, read
		<a href="/how-this-site-writes-itself/">how this site writes itself</a>.
	</p>

	<h2>Work with us</h2>
	<p>
		If your team wants to put agents to work — on the phones, the follow-ups, the scheduling, the
		busywork — we design and ship those systems. Tell us what you're trying to automate and a real
		person will read it and reply.
	</p>
	<p>
		<a class="button" href="/contact/">Get in touch</a>
	</p>
</Layout>
